# Database schema

- This is **WordPress**, not Laravel. We use Laravel structure (Eloquent, etc.) for **code only**, not for database creation.
- Do **not** add a Laravel-style migration system (multiple migration files, artisan migrate, migration runners, or versioned migrations).
- All custom database tables must be defined in **one SQL file** (e.g. `schema.sql` or `database/schema.sql`). That file is the single source of truth for creating/updating custom table structure.
- Run it **manually** (phpMyAdmin, CLI, or one-off script) when schema changes. Use plain SQL (`CREATE TABLE`, indexes, FKs). No migration runner or framework schema builder.
- For EscapeZoom, the single source of truth for all `wp_ez_*` tables is **`wp-content/mu-plugins/escapezoom-core/database/schema.sql`**. Do not use Laravel migrations (e.g. `php artisan migrate` or files under `database/migrations`) to create or alter `wp_ez_*` tables. The folder `vendor/illuminate/database/Migrations/stubs` contains Laravel’s generic migration templates; do not delete it (it is part of Illuminate), and do not use those stubs for EscapeZoom schema — only `schema.sql` defines EZ tables.
